  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went to Cape Town, but I couldn't leave the boat in Cape Town But I could see the beautiful city and the mountains there, with the flat top.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we came to Mozambique.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, in Mozambique, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was suppose to wait for a ship that was to Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was very difficult, but they said there will be ships with your part of it, maybe to Singapore, and from Singapore you can go to Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I knew that the Shanghai visa was worth nothing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You could come on the land way to Shanghai, but only from the sea, you couldn't.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You had to go through-- The people in Shanghai who-- the people who had issued me the visa for Shanghai were not the people in power anymore in China.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they couldn't do it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, fortunately, the consul, the American consul to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Laurenco Marques was a very friendly man, very good man, and we ate in the same restaurant before.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had met an acquaintance there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next day I came, and he asked me what my plans are.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, I would like to get into the United States.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On the ship, on the-- [INAUDIBLE] was the name of the ship-- I had met Mr.-- I forgot the name.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe it comes to my mind-- who was a very, very well known farmer-- a big farmer-- in Israel, in Palestine, and very, very known, politically, quite an important figure.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he told me, you will never get to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wanted to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have to go around the East Coast of Africa, everywhere the British are the pwer.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
